        "created_at": "2025-11-21T06:07:46.638Z",
        "cooked": "<p>The new poll feature is very cool! I‚Äôm excited to use them to annoy and delight my friends. However, it has strange behavior when editing individual options.</p>\n<p>If I have a poll with multiple options and I delete all of the text of one of them, that option is immediately removed and I‚Äôm editing the beginning of the next option. This means if I want to re-type a whole option, I need to delicately select all but one letter, write the new text, and then delete the initial letter so it doesn‚Äôt move places.</p>\n<p>Additionally, there‚Äôs no way to reposition options, so if I delete all text from an option and it‚Äôs removed, I have to delete all follow-up options to put my desired option next.</p>\n<p>I can‚Äôt attach a video or I‚Äôd demonstrate for you the behavior here.</p>\n<p>My ideal UX would be that there are <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/images/emoji/apple/cross_mark_button.png?v=14\" title=\":cross_mark_button:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":cross_mark_button:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"> buttons at the end of each poll option which controls it being deleted, and that long-clicking an option lets you reorder it.</p>\n<p>If the current behavior of ‚Äúan empty option is removed‚Äù is to be maintained, can removal happen when it loses focus? That way, you can ctrl-a to select all of the text and rewrite it without losing the place.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 3,
