        "created_at": "2025-11-21T06:13:04.788Z",
        "cooked": "<p>That sounds like a bug that needs to be reported on GitHub.</p>\n<p>The Android app allows fully deleting the text and the option will remain unless you move focus out of it while it is empty.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"NoahTheDuke\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"73029\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/noahtheduke/48/52188_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> NoahTheDuke:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This means if I want to re-type a whole option, I need to delicately select all but one letter, write the new text, and then delete the initial letter so it doesn‚Äôt move places.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I suspect that as a simpler workaround, you could just select all the text, then begin typing to avoid the item disappearing.</p>",
